WEBVTT

00:00.890 --> 00:02.027
- CORY SMITH.
- MY NEW BOSS.

00:02.070 --> 00:03.207
- WE'RE GOING TO BE GOING

00:03.240 --> 00:05.515
FOR AN EXTREMELY
YOUTH-ORIENTED PRODUCT,

00:05.550 --> 00:07.199
AND IT IS GOING
TO GET RADICAL.

00:07.240 --> 00:09.105
- I GOT IT, I GOT IT.

00:09.140 --> 00:11.074
WHEN YOU REGAIN OUR TRUST,
YOU CAN HAVE YOUR DOOR BACK.

00:11.110 --> 00:12.077
- YOU GUYS
HAVE GONE CRAZY.

00:12.110 --> 00:13.839
- IF THINGS ARE GONNA
WORK OUT BETWEEN US,

00:13.870 --> 00:15.451
YOU GOT TO MAKE THINGS RIGHT
WITH YOUR FOLKS.

00:15.490 --> 00:17.833
I MISS YOU.

00:17.870 --> 00:19.735
- WHEN YOU TELL A TEENAGE GIRL
THAT SHE CAN'T HAVE SOMETHING,

00:19.770 --> 00:21.146
SHE'S GONNA WANT IT
EVEN MORE.

00:21.190 --> 00:22.464
I MEAN, YOU KNOW THAT.
- RIGHT.

00:22.500 --> 00:23.637
- WHAT'S GOING ON?

00:23.670 --> 00:25.399
- CAN I STAY HERE
FOR A WHILE?

00:25.430 --> 00:26.749
- HOW LONG A WHILE?

00:26.780 --> 00:28.634
- COLLEGE.

00:34.240 --> 00:37.300
- HEY, MAXIMO,
LOOK AT THIS.

00:37.340 --> 00:38.511
YOU REMEMBER THIS?

00:38.550 --> 00:40.165
- UH, YEAH.
YEAH, I DO.

00:40.210 --> 00:42.303
- YOUR DAD CAUGHT A TROUT
WITH THIS BABY

00:42.350 --> 00:43.681
ON HIS FIRST
CAMPING EXPERIENCE.

00:43.730 --> 00:45.755
YOU READY TO CATCH
SOME FISH, MAX?

00:45.800 --> 00:46.789
- NOT REALLY.

00:46.830 --> 00:48.343
- OH, COME ON,
JUST WAIT TILL WE GET OUT THERE.

00:48.390 --> 00:49.459
IT'S GONNA BE FUN.

00:49.490 --> 00:50.696
TELL HIM IT'S GONNA
BE FUN, ADAM.

00:50.740 --> 00:51.866
- MAX, IT'S GONNA BE FUN.

00:51.910 --> 00:53.423
- TELL HIM
MORE ENTHUSIASTICALLY.

00:53.460 --> 00:55.280
- IT'S GONNA BE FUN, MAX.
- YEAH, IT'S GONNA BE FUN.

00:55.330 --> 00:56.490
IT'S PART OF THE WHOLE

00:56.530 --> 00:59.533
BRAVERMAN MALE-BON DING
CAMPING EXPERIENCE.

00:59.570 --> 01:01.811
YOU KNOW, WE GET TO CATCH OUR--
CATCH OUR DINNER

01:01.850 --> 01:03.260
AND COOK IT ON A FIRE

01:03.300 --> 01:04.779
AND SLEEP
UNDER THE STARS.

01:04.820 --> 01:06.674
HUH? YOU READY TO DO
SOME BONDING, MAX?

01:06.720 --> 01:08.369
- UH-HUH.

01:08.410 --> 01:10.640
- IT'S GONNA BE ONE
OF THE FIVE BEST MOMENTS

01:10.690 --> 01:12.578
OF YOUR LIFE, GRANDSON.
- YEP.

01:12.620 --> 01:13.518
- YOU KNOW, GRANDMA'S MAKING

01:13.550 --> 01:15.097
HER WAFFLES
WITH THE CHOCOLATE CHIPS,

01:15.140 --> 01:18.587
SO I'M GONNA GO INSIDE.
- ALL RIGHT, GO AHEAD.

01:18.630 --> 01:20.825
LISTEN, DAD,
ABOUT THE FISHING--

01:20.870 --> 01:22.724
I JUST WANT YOU
TO UNDERSTAND, YOU KNOW,

01:22.770 --> 01:24.726
IT'S A LONG TIME FOR HIM
TO BE SITTING DOWN AND WAITING,

01:24.770 --> 01:26.624
AND MAX LIKES THINGS
TO HAPPEN RIGHT AWAY.

01:26.670 --> 01:28.638
- OH, HE'S GONNA BE FINE, SON.
HE'S GONNA BE FINE.

01:28.670 --> 01:30.592
YOU AND KRISTINA--
YOU WORRY TOO MUCH.

01:30.640 --> 01:31.629
- LISTEN, DAD, WE JUST--

01:31.670 --> 01:34.366
WE JUST WANT YOU TO HAVE
A SUCCESSFUL TRIP, OKAY?

01:34.400 --> 01:36.436
SO THAT'S...

01:36.470 --> 01:39.223
WHY KRISTINA
PUT THIS TOGETHER FOR YOU.

01:39.270 --> 01:41.158
IF YOU COULD
JUST GIVE IT A READ.

01:41.200 --> 01:42.929
- NOW, WHAT THE HELL
IS THIS?

01:42.960 --> 01:45.269
- IT'S JUST A SET
OF, YOU KNOW, GUIDELINES

01:45.310 --> 01:48.234
TO HELP YOU AND MAX
HAVE A SUCCESSFUL TRIP.

01:48.280 --> 01:50.373
- OH, NOW, I DON'T NEED
AN INSTRUCTION MANUAL

01:50.420 --> 01:52.138
TO TAKE MY GRANDSON CAMPING
FOR ONE NIGHT, SON.

01:52.180 --> 01:53.659
- ACTUALLY, YOU DO.

01:53.690 --> 01:55.271
- HUH.
- OKAY?

01:55.320 --> 01:58.289
- WELL, WORRY NOT, MY SON.

01:58.320 --> 02:01.187
- WORRY I WILL,
MY FATHER.

02:04.840 --> 02:07.252
- OH, BOY.
THIS IS WORSE THAN I THOUGHT.

02:07.290 --> 02:07.972
- YEAH.

02:09.470 --> 02:10.676
- OH, MY GOD,
IT'S SCENTED.

02:10.710 --> 02:11.916
- YEAH.
[laughing]

02:11.950 --> 02:13.747
- OH, BOY.

02:13.780 --> 02:15.475
- OH! JULIA.

02:15.510 --> 02:17.159
- WELL, CONGRATULATIONS.

02:17.200 --> 02:18.337
- SHE'S SUCH A SWEETHEART

02:18.370 --> 02:19.849
FOR THROWING ME
AN ENGAGEMENT PARTY,

02:19.890 --> 02:21.403
BUT I HAVE TO ADMIT,

02:21.450 --> 02:22.678
SHE KIND OF SCARES ME
A LITTLE BIT.

02:22.720 --> 02:24.369
- OH, JULIA SCARES YOU.
- YEAH.

02:24.420 --> 02:25.853
- I'VE NEVER HEARD
THAT BEFORE.

02:25.900 --> 02:28.175
- "PASSED HORS D'OEUVRES,
FORMAL DINNER,

02:28.210 --> 02:28.960
PARTY GAMES"?

02:29.010 --> 02:30.409
EMBOSSED INVITATION?

02:30.460 --> 02:32.280
THERE'S ONLY GONNA BE,
LIKE, FIVE PEOPLE THERE.

02:32.320 --> 02:33.389
I MEAN, ISN'T THIS
A BIT MUCH?

02:33.420 --> 02:35.980
I MEAN, I'M APPRECIATIVE
FOR HER DOING THIS FOR ME,

02:36.010 --> 02:36.908
BUT I'M FINE WITH PIZZA.

02:36.940 --> 02:39.181
I'M SIMPLE.
I DON'T NEED A BIG TO-DO.

02:39.220 --> 02:42.189
- YOU UNDERSTAND THIS PARTY
ISN'T ABOUT YOU, RIGHT?

02:42.230 --> 02:43.561
- YEAH, IT IS.

02:43.610 --> 02:46.704
IT'S THE BRAVER-WOMEN
INVITING ME INTO THEIR TRIBE.

02:46.750 --> 02:47.978
- NO, NO, THIS--

02:48.020 --> 02:50.193
THIS PARTY'S ABOUT JULIA
PROVING SOMETHING.

02:50.230 --> 02:51.265
- PROVING WHAT?

02:51.300 --> 02:52.619
- WELL, THAT'S NOT CLEAR
JUST YET,

02:52.650 --> 02:55.164
BUT BELIEVE ME,
SHE'S OUT TO PROVE SOMETHING.

02:58.240 --> 03:00.720
- ENOUGH IS ENOUGH, RIGHT?

03:00.760 --> 03:02.682
IT'S BEEN TWO DAYS,
AND I WANT HER HOME.

03:02.730 --> 03:05.244
THIS IS RIDICULOUS.
- YEAH.

03:05.280 --> 03:07.339
BUT WE CAN'T JUST DRAG
HER HOME.

03:07.390 --> 03:08.550
- WHY NOT?

03:08.600 --> 03:10.488
- 'CAUSE SHE'LL JUST
LEAVE AGAIN.

03:10.530 --> 03:14.466
- I'M SURE YOUR MOM'S HAVING
ONE BIG PARTY OVER THERE.

03:14.500 --> 03:15.842
- KRISTINA, COME ON,
YOU KNOW,

03:15.880 --> 03:17.700
MY MOM'S NOT
ON HADDIE'S SIDE HERE.

03:17.740 --> 03:19.298
- OH, YES, SHE IS.

03:19.330 --> 03:21.890
SHE REALLY IS.

03:21.920 --> 03:23.296
- LOOK, KRISTINA,
I JUST--

03:23.340 --> 03:24.568
I DON'T WANT
TO SHOW UP THERE

03:24.610 --> 03:26.407
AND MAKE THINGS WORSE
BY FORCING THE ISSUE.

03:26.440 --> 03:28.328
THAT'S ALL I'M SAYING.

03:28.380 --> 03:29.859
- OKAY, WELL, SHE'S 16.

03:29.890 --> 03:32.279
SHE'S OUR DAUGHTER,
AND I WANT HER HOME.

03:32.310 --> 03:34.301
- I'M NOT A GHOST
IN THIS TOWN

03:34.350 --> 03:37.626
- ALL RIGHT.
[doorbell rings]

03:41.040 --> 03:42.769
- WHAT'S WITH THE DOORBELL?

03:42.800 --> 03:43.789
COME ON IN.

03:43.840 --> 03:46.877
- UH, THANKS,
BUT WE'RE, UH...

03:46.910 --> 03:49.014
WE'RE HERE
TO TALK TO HADDIE,

03:49.050 --> 03:50.665
PRIVATELY,
IF YOU WOULDN'T MIND.

03:50.710 --> 03:51.870
- SURE, I'LL GET HER.

03:51.920 --> 03:54.775
- THANKS, MOM.
- THANK YOU.

03:54.820 --> 03:57.391
AWIQNARD.

04:04.930 --> 04:06.306
- HEY.
- HEY.

04:06.340 --> 04:08.274
- CAN WE TALK TO YOU?

04:08.310 --> 04:10.346
- PRIVATELY, OUTSIDE?

04:10.380 --> 04:12.348
- OKAY.

04:20.600 --> 04:22.283
- WE WANT YOU
TO COME HOME.

04:22.330 --> 04:24.469
- WELL, YOU KNOW
MY CONDITION.

04:24.500 --> 04:25.979
- HADDIE, COME ON,
WE'RE YOUR PARENTS, OKAY?

04:26.020 --> 04:27.806
WE'RE NOT HERE TO NEGOTIATE.
- ABSOLUTELY NOT.

04:27.850 --> 04:30.956
- WELL, I'M NOT GONNA COME HOME
UNTIL I CAN SEE ALEX.

04:30.990 --> 04:32.673
- HADDIE, I KNOW
THAT YOU THINK YOU'RE AN ADULT

04:32.720 --> 04:34.506
AND YOU CAN MAKE UP
YOUR OWN MIND ABOUT THINGS.

04:34.550 --> 04:35.744
BUT YOU'RE NOT.
YOU'RE 16.

04:35.790 --> 04:37.678
AND YOU LIVE IN OUR HOUSE.
- ABSOLUTELY.

04:37.720 --> 04:39.995
- WELL, NOT RIGHT NOW.
THAT'S WHY I'M NOT THERE.

04:40.030 --> 04:42.089
- YOU'RE ACTING LIKE A BABY.

04:42.140 --> 04:44.108
YOU'RE NOT GONNA DATE ALEX
ACTING LIKE THIS.

04:44.140 --> 04:45.516
THIS IS RIDICULOUS.

04:45.560 --> 04:46.629
- DAD?

04:46.660 --> 04:47.729
- YEAH?

04:47.770 --> 04:49.340
- IS THIS THE WAY
THAT YOU FEEL

04:49.390 --> 04:51.005
AFI'ER ALEX
WENT TO TALK TO YOU?

04:54.880 --> 04:56.973
- I LIKE ALEX, OKAY?

04:57.020 --> 04:58.089
I DON'T THINK

04:58.120 --> 04:59.633
IT'S AN APPROPRIATE RELATIONSHIP
FOR YOU,

04:59.670 --> 05:01.399
AND I THINK THAT STAYING HERE
IS A STUNT.

05:01.430 --> 05:02.670
- WHY DON'T WE HAVE
A CONVERSATION

05:02.710 --> 05:05.122
ABOUT WHAT IT IS THAT MAKES
YOU UNCOMFORTABLE ABOUT ALEX?

05:05.160 --> 05:06.195
- WE HAD A CONVERSATION

05:06.230 --> 05:08.118
ABOUT WHAT MAKES US
UNCOMFORTABLE ABOUT ALEX.

05:08.160 --> 05:09.092
- BUT WE CAN GET PAST IT

05:09.130 --> 05:10.882
IF YOU JUST TALK ABOUT IT
AND DON'T JUST--

05:10.930 --> 05:12.500
- YOU'RE 16 YEARS OLD.
YOU'RE A JUNIOR IN HIGH SCHOOL.

05:12.550 --> 05:13.778
HE'S 19.
HE LIVES IN AN APARTMENT.

05:13.830 --> 05:14.717
- WHAT ABOUT HIM
BEING BLACK?

05:14.760 --> 05:16.512
- THAT HAS NOTHING
TO DO WITH IT, OKAY?

05:16.550 --> 05:17.994
PLEASE DON'T EVER BRING
THAT UP AGAIN.

05:18.040 --> 05:19.519
- WE'RE NOT RACIST, OKAY?

05:19.560 --> 05:21.061
- WELL, THEN...
- YOU'RE 16.

05:21.110 --> 05:22.418
HE'S 19, OKAY?

05:22.460 --> 05:24.599
- I MEAN,
I'VE HEARD THIS BEFORE.

05:24.630 --> 05:27.383
- HE'S AN ALCOHOLIC,
AND YOU'RE NOT AN ALCOHOLIC.

05:27.430 --> 05:29.148
- STOP SAYING THINGS
THAT ARE JUST WRONG WITH HIM.

05:29.190 --> 05:30.691
THIS IS SOMEBODY
THAT I CARE ABOUT

05:30.740 --> 05:32.082
THAT I WANT TO BE WITH.

05:33.780 --> 05:35.395
- [sighs]

05:35.430 --> 05:37.113
- YOU WANT TO BE WITH HIM?

05:37.160 --> 05:38.536
- YES.

05:38.570 --> 05:41.403
- MORE THAN YOU
WANT TO BE WITH US?

05:42.610 --> 05:43.599
- YES.

05:43.650 --> 05:45.993
- THERE'S NOTHING ELSE
TO SAY.

05:46.030 --> 05:47.850
- I AGREE.

05:47.890 --> 05:49.130
EXCUSE ME.

05:51.170 --> 05:53.411
[door opens]

05:53.450 --> 05:55.554
[door slams]

05:55.590 --> 05:58.479
- MAY GOD BLESS
AND KEEP YOU ALWAYS

05:58.530 --> 06:01.044
AND MAY YOUR WISHES
ALL COME TRUE

06:01.080 --> 06:03.184
MAY YOU ALWAYS DO
FOR OTHERS

06:03.220 --> 06:05.768
AND LET OTHERS DO FOR YOU

06:05.810 --> 06:08.187
MAY YOU BUILD A LADDER
TO THE STARS

06:08.220 --> 06:10.427
AND CLIMB ON EVERY RUNG

06:10.470 --> 06:12.563
AND MAY YOU STAY

06:12.610 --> 06:15.431
FOREVER YOUNG

06:15.470 --> 06:18.098
MAY YOU GROW UP
TO BE RIGHTEOUS

06:18.130 --> 06:20.507
MAY YOU GROW UP
TO BE TRUE

06:20.550 --> 06:22.859
MAY YOU ALWAYS KNOW
THE TRUTH

06:22.890 --> 06:25.063
AND SEE THE LIGHTS
SURROUNDING YOU

06:25.100 --> 06:27.864
MAY YOU ALWAYS BE
COURAGEOUS

06:27.900 --> 06:30.039
STAND UPRIGHT
AND BE STRONG

06:30.070 --> 06:32.004
AND MAY YOU STAY

06:32.040 --> 06:34.691
FOREVER YOUNG

06:34.730 --> 06:36.766
MAY YOU STAY

06:36.810 --> 06:39.426
FOREVER YOUNG

06:42.950 --> 06:43.974
- PERFORMANCE--EXCELLENT.

06:44.020 --> 06:45.226
FRIENDLINESS--GREAT.

06:45.260 --> 06:46.670
PRODUCT IVITY--EXCELLENT.

06:46.710 --> 06:47.938
TIM ELIN ESS--SPORADIC.

06:47.990 --> 06:49.708
- SPORADIC?
- WHAT?

06:49.750 --> 06:50.956
- BUT I'M ALMOST
ALWAYS ON TIME.

06:50.990 --> 06:52.855
- ALMOST ALWAYS
IS NOT ALWAYS ON TIME.

06:52.890 --> 06:54.778
LISTEN, SARAH,
YOU'RE THE ONE

06:54.820 --> 06:55.923
WHO REQUESTED
A PERFORMANCE REVIEW,

06:55.960 --> 06:57.757
WHICH WE DON'T NORMALLY DO
FOR INTERNS.

06:57.790 --> 06:59.542
- NO, I KNOW, BUTI NEED
A GOOD PERFORMANCE REVIEW.

06:59.590 --> 07:01.649
I'M TRYING
TO GET A RAISE HERE, YOU KNOW.

07:01.690 --> 07:03.931
DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA
HOW MUCH BERKELEY COSTS A YEAR?

07:03.970 --> 07:05.858
- YEAH, IT'S LIKE 25 GRAND
A YEAR WITH ROOM AND BOARD.

07:05.900 --> 07:07.458
- OKAY, YOU KNOW
HOW MUCH OF THAT

07:07.490 --> 07:09.481
I HAVE SAVED
FOR AMBER'S COLLEGE EDUCATION?

07:09.530 --> 07:10.736
- LISTEN, SARAH,
I HAD TO FIRE

07:10.770 --> 07:11.930
A QUARTER
OF THE WORKFORCE HERE.

07:11.980 --> 07:13.527
- I KNOW, BUT...

07:13.570 --> 07:15.492
SHOULDN'T THOSE OF US
WHO MADE THE CUT

07:15.530 --> 07:17.669
BE CELEBRATED?

07:17.710 --> 07:19.849
TOO SOON?
- YEAH.

07:19.880 --> 07:21.814
LISTEN, SARAH, EVEN
IF WE COULD GIVE YOU A RAISE,

07:21.850 --> 07:24.193
WHICH WE CAN'T,
I'M IN BIZARRO-LAND

07:24.230 --> 07:26.744
WITH THIS GUY HERE, OKAY?

07:26.790 --> 07:27.859
I MEAN, MY PLATE
IS FULL ENOUGH

07:27.890 --> 07:29.881
TRYING TO KEEP BOY BLUNDER
FROM SINKING THE SHIP.

07:29.930 --> 07:31.158
- WHAT IS HE DOING?
- I DON'T KNOW.

07:31.200 --> 07:34.203
- WHAT IS HE--
OH, HEY.

07:34.240 --> 07:36.754
WHAT IS THAT?

07:36.800 --> 07:38.131
IS THAT "ROCK ON"?

07:38.180 --> 07:40.136
- THIS IS "HANG LOOSE."
THAT'S "ROCK ON."

07:40.180 --> 07:41.579
- OH.

07:41.630 --> 07:44.599
[jazz music playing]

07:44.630 --> 07:46.803
- [exhales deeply]
OKAY, YOU KNOW WHAT?

07:46.840 --> 07:48.876
YOU AND ADAM AND CROSBY

07:48.910 --> 07:51.185
CAN STAY OUT DRINKING
TILL AFI'ER MIDNIGHT.

07:51.220 --> 07:53.848
YOU KNOW, HAVE FUN, 'CAUSE THE
GIRLS ARE GONNA BE HAVING FUN...

07:53.880 --> 07:54.869
- IF WE MUST.
- HERE.

07:54.920 --> 07:55.841
- UH-HUH.

07:55.880 --> 07:58.269
- OH, GOSH, THIS IS
SO IMPORTANT TO ME.

07:58.300 --> 08:00.746
- CLEARLY.
WE STILL GOT TWO DAYS, HON.

08:00.790 --> 08:02.234
- [sighs] I JUST--
I WANT IT TO BE AWESOME.

08:02.270 --> 08:03.339
- IT WILL BE, HONEY.

08:03.370 --> 08:06.646
- I KNOW. I JUST--
I WANT THEM TO LEAVE AND SAY,

08:06.690 --> 08:07.850
"I CAN'T BELIEVE
I EVER THOUGHT

08:07.900 --> 08:09.583
THAT IT WAS NOT GONNA BE FUN
AT JULIA'S."

08:09.620 --> 08:10.928
- I'M SURE
THEY DON'T THINK THAT.

08:10.970 --> 08:12.961
- I KNOW.
I'M SURE THEY DON'T.

08:13.000 --> 08:15.173
AND YET, THEY GO
TO MOM AND DAD'S,

08:15.210 --> 08:16.859
AND THEY GO
TO ADAM AND KRISTINA'S,

08:16.910 --> 08:18.525
AND THEY DON'T COME HERE.

08:18.560 --> 08:20.619
- WELL, IT'S PROBABLY 'CAUSE
WE'RE KIND OF OUT OF THE WAY.

08:20.670 --> 08:21.807
- NO, LET'S BE HONEST.

08:21.840 --> 08:22.943
THEY NEED TO KNOW
THAT IT'S FUN HERE.

08:22.980 --> 08:24.732
- IT IS FUN HERE.
- IT'S FUN HERE.

08:24.780 --> 08:25.735
- IT'S TONS OF FUN HERE.
- IT IS.

08:25.780 --> 08:26.735
- YOU, ME, A SIX-YEAR-OLD.

08:26.780 --> 08:29.089
- I HAVE HORS D'OEUVRES
FOR THE LIVING ROOM

08:29.120 --> 08:30.815
AND THEN A SIT-DOWN DINNER.
- YOU DO.

08:30.850 --> 08:32.192
- AND THEN
I HAVE PARTY GAMES.

08:32.230 --> 08:33.572
- OH RE--
PARTY GAMES?

08:33.610 --> 08:35.783
- MM-HMM.
- YOU DON'T THINK THAT SOUNDS

08:35.820 --> 08:37.048
A LITTLE, UH...?
- WHAT?

08:37.100 --> 08:38.852
- UH, JUST PLANNED.

08:41.760 --> 08:43.091
- IT WON'T FEEL PLANNED.

08:43.140 --> 08:44.960
IT'S GONNA--
IT'S GONNA FLOW NICELY

08:45.000 --> 08:46.797
AND FEEL VERY NATURAL AND FUN.
- YEAH.

08:46.830 --> 08:49.037
- AND A GOOD PARTY
NEEDS STRUCTURE.

08:49.080 --> 08:50.104
- MM.
- YEAH.

08:50.150 --> 08:52.004
- OKAY.

08:52.040 --> 08:53.280
YEAH.

08:56.910 --> 08:59.708
- KRISTINA.
[chuckles]

08:59.740 --> 09:01.355
HI.
- OH, HEY.

09:01.400 --> 09:03.015
UM, CAN I COME IN?

09:03.050 --> 09:04.563
- OF COURSE.
- THANK YOU.

09:04.610 --> 09:05.565
IJUST, UM...

09:05.610 --> 09:07.953
I WANTED TO DROP OFF
SOME CLOTHES FOR HADDIE.

09:07.990 --> 09:09.127
- OH.
- YEAH.

09:09.160 --> 09:10.980
I'M SURE SHE'S BORROWING
ALL OF AMBER'S.

09:11.030 --> 09:12.884
- GOOD IDEA.
SHE'LL BE HAPPY TO SEE THOSE.

09:12.930 --> 09:15.194
- YEAH. I ALSO WANT TO GIVE YOU,
UM, SOME MONEY.

09:15.240 --> 09:16.889
- OH, NO, NO.
- I'M SURE SHE'S BEEN EATING YOU

09:16.930 --> 09:18.204
OUT OF HOUISIEAND HOME.

09:18.240 --> 09:21.937
- SO JUST A COUPLE BUCKS.
- NO, I'M NOT TAKING IT.

09:21.970 --> 09:23.244
BUT COULD WE TALK

09:23.280 --> 09:25.145
JUST FOR A MINUTE?

09:25.180 --> 09:29.731
- YEAH, SURE.

09:29.770 --> 09:31.909
- WE'RE BOTH ON THE SAME SIDE
HERE, YOU KNOW.

09:31.950 --> 09:33.599
RIGHT?

09:33.640 --> 09:35.733
WE BOTH JUST WANT
WHAT'S BEST FOR HADDIE.

09:35.780 --> 09:37.088
- I KNOW. I-I DO.

09:37.120 --> 09:39.008
WE BOTH DO.
I'M JUST--I'M UPSET AT HER,

09:39.060 --> 09:41.221
AND I'M TAKING IT OUT ON YOU,
AND I DON'T MEAN TO.

09:41.270 --> 09:43.056
I DON'T.
- IT'S OKAY, REALLY.

09:43.090 --> 09:44.739
- OKAY.
- DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.

09:44.790 --> 09:45.950
- THANKS.

