- COME ON, MAX.
COME ON.

19:32.860 --> 19:33.929
- HEY.
- HI.

19:33.960 --> 19:35.507
- EVERYTHING ALL RIGHT?
- YEAH.

19:35.550 --> 19:36.949
- NEED ANYTHING?
- NOPE.

19:37.000 --> 19:39.343
- YOUR BROTHER MISSES YOU.
- THANKS FOR THE CLOTHES.

19:39.380 --> 19:40.586
- SHE OKAY?

19:40.620 --> 19:42.929
[horn honks]
- OKAY.

19:42.970 --> 19:43.891
- BYE, BUDDY.

19:43.940 --> 19:45.862
- ADIOS, AMIGOS!
- OKAY, HAVE FUN.

19:45.900 --> 19:47.595
JUST DRIVE SAFELY,
ALL RIGHT, POP?

19:47.630 --> 19:48.858
[tires squealing]

19:48.910 --> 19:50.901
- OH, MY GOD.

19:50.940 --> 19:52.384
OH, DEAR GOD.

19:52.430 --> 19:54.591
- BYE.

20:08.480 --> 20:10.710
- OHH.
- YOU ALL RIGHT?

20:10.760 --> 20:12.022
- I DON'T KNOW, HONEY.

20:12.070 --> 20:13.617
SOMETHING
JUST CAME OVER ME.

20:13.660 --> 20:16.276
I'M LIKE...

20:16.310 --> 20:17.868
CAN YOU FEEL MY FOREHEAD...

20:17.900 --> 20:19.276
- YEAH.
- JUST FOR A SECOND?

20:19.320 --> 20:20.764
LIKE, I'M--
IT'S ALL PAIN.

20:20.800 --> 20:22.483
- LET'S SEE.
- LIKE, RIGHT HERE.

20:22.530 --> 20:24.691
- OH, YEAH. OOH, I DON'T WANT
TO GET TOO CLOSE,

20:24.740 --> 20:27.459
'CAUSE YOU'VE DEFINITELY
GOT A BAD CASE

20:27.500 --> 20:29.047
OF "I DON'T WANT TO GO
TO THIS PARTY-ITIS."

20:29.080 --> 20:31.048
A SEVERE CASE.
- OKAY, YOU KNOW WHAT?

20:31.090 --> 20:33.251
- WHAT?
- I DON'T WANT TO GO.

20:33.300 --> 20:35.564
I CAN'T GO THERE
AND ACT LIKE EVERYTHING'S OKAY.

20:35.610 --> 20:37.601
OKAY? JULIA WILL UNDERSTAND.
IT'S FINE.

20:37.650 --> 20:39.026
- OH, YEAH.
COME ON, I MEAN, IT'S JULIA.

20:39.060 --> 20:41.642
I MEAN, SHE'S THE MOST
EASYGOING PERSON IN THE WORLD.

20:43.310 --> 20:45.028
- HONEY, HADDIE
LOOKED SO HAPPY.

20:45.070 --> 20:46.992
- YEAH.

20:47.030 --> 20:50.272
[cell phone rings]

20:50.310 --> 20:52.039
HOLD ON.

20:52.070 --> 20:53.628
- WHO IS THAT?
- HEY. HELLO?

20:53.660 --> 20:55.070
- ZEEK?
- WHAT'S UP?

20:55.110 --> 20:56.338
- IS MAX OKAY?

20:56.390 --> 20:58.278
- YEAH.
- IS IT JULIA?

20:58.320 --> 20:59.480
THE PARTY'S CANCELED,
ISN'T IT?

20:59.530 --> 21:00.690
- NO, I GET IT, I THINK.

21:00.740 --> 21:02.389
- I BET THE PARTY'S CANCELED.

21:02.430 --> 21:03.283
I DON'T HAVE TO GO.
- OKAY, ALL RIGHT.

21:03.330 --> 21:04.422
NO, IT'S NOT A PROBLEM.

21:04.470 --> 21:05.801
I WILL BE THERE
AS SOON AS I CAN, OKAY?

21:05.850 --> 21:07.078
ALL RIGHT, BYE.
- WHO WAS THAT?

21:07.120 --> 21:08.155
- THAT WAS CORY FROM WORK.

21:08.190 --> 21:09.771
HE WANTS ME TO COME
TO THE OFFICE IMMEDIATELY.

21:09.820 --> 21:11.321
- IT'S SATURDAY. WHY ARE YOU--
- YEAH, I KNOW.

21:11.370 --> 21:13.361
BECAUSE HE SAYS
HE'S FIGURED IT ALL OUT.

21:13.410 --> 21:14.434
- FIGURED WHAT OUT?

21:14.480 --> 21:17.301
- SHOES.

21:17.340 --> 21:19.308
- HEY, MAX, COME HERE

21:19.340 --> 21:20.989
AND HELP ME
SET UP THE TENT, WILL YOU?

21:21.030 --> 21:22.304
AND THEN
WE CAN GO FISHING.

21:22.350 --> 21:23.999
- YOU SAID
WE COULD LOOK FOR BUGS.

21:24.040 --> 21:26.349
- YEAH, BUT I THINK
WE SHOULD GET THE CAMP READY

21:26.380 --> 21:28.416
WHILE WE STILL
HAVE LIGHT HERE, GRANDSON.

21:28.450 --> 21:29.838
- I WANT TO LOOK
FOR BUGS NOW, THOUGH.

21:29.870 --> 21:33.351
- WELL, MAXIMO, I COULD
REALLY USE YOUR HELP OVER HERE.

21:33.390 --> 21:35.073
COME ON, NOW.
WE'RE A TEAM.

21:35.120 --> 21:37.327
- IF WE'RE A TEAM, THEN HOW
ABOUT WE LOOK FOR BUGS FIRST,

21:37.360 --> 21:39.043
THEN SET UP THE TENT?

21:42.160 --> 21:43.149
- WHY CAN'T WE EAT ANYTHING?

21:43.190 --> 21:45.363
- BECAUSE I'M SURE
SHE'LL BE HERE ANY MINUTE,

21:45.400 --> 21:46.298
AND THEN SHE GETS TO SEE...
- WE CAN'T EAT THAT?

21:46.330 --> 21:47.365
- HOW BEAUTIFULLY
IT'S ALL PRESENTED.

21:47.400 --> 21:49.960
- WHAT ABOUT THAT?
- NOT GETTING ANYTHING YET.

21:49.990 --> 21:52.436
- JULES, CAN I GET
A LITTLE MORE?

21:52.480 --> 21:53.993
- YEAH. IS IT MINTY ENOUGH?
- IT'S DELICIOUS.

21:54.030 --> 21:56.407
- DID CROSBY TELL YOU ABOUT ALL
HER FOOD ALLERGIES AND STUFF?

21:56.450 --> 21:58.759
- WHAT?
- DAIRY, NUTS, SHELLFISH.

21:58.800 --> 22:00.654
- ARE YOU KIDDING?
I MADE--

22:00.690 --> 22:02.624
OKAY, I MADE CRAB CAKES.
- LEMONS, LIMES.

22:02.660 --> 22:03.968
- THAT'S EVERYTHING.

22:04.010 --> 22:06.478
THAT'S DAIRY.
SHE'S GOT SOMETHING, I THINK.

22:06.530 --> 22:08.145
- [laughing]

22:08.180 --> 22:09.693
- IT'S JUST SO EASY.

22:09.740 --> 22:11.116
IT'S LIKE SHOOTING
FISH IN A BARREL.

22:11.150 --> 22:12.629
- YOU'RE A BAD, BAD PERSON.

22:12.670 --> 22:14.399
- IT LOOKS REALLY GOOD.
I CAN'T WAIT TO EAT.

22:14.430 --> 22:16.534
- YEAH, IT'S DELICIOUS.
I DON'T DESERVE THAT.

22:18.500 --> 22:19.569
IT'S JUST LIKE--

22:19.610 --> 22:22.158
- HADDIE'S DOING WELL,
YOU KNOW, SO DON'T WORRY.

22:22.200 --> 22:24.361
I KNOW IT'S CRAZY,
BUT SHE'S DOING GREAT.

22:24.410 --> 22:25.399
- THANKS.
THANKS FOR, UM,

22:25.440 --> 22:28.159
YOU KNOW, LOOKING OUT FOR HER.
APPRECIATE IT.

22:28.200 --> 22:30.407
- I'VE BEEN THERE.
- YEAH.

22:30.450 --> 22:33.101
- YOU KNOW, IF I TOLD YOU
HOW MANY TIMES

22:33.140 --> 22:34.892
THIS ONE HERE
RAN AWAY FROM HOME...

22:34.930 --> 22:36.409
- MOM.
- YOU WOULDN'T BELIEVE IT.

22:36.450 --> 22:37.314
- NOT THIS ONE.
- NOT THAT ONE.

22:37.350 --> 22:39.386
- YOU MANAGED SOMEHOW
TO MAKE ME FEEL

22:39.420 --> 22:41.559
LIKE A REALLY ROTTEN MOTHER,
YOU KNOW?

22:41.600 --> 22:42.999
- SORRY.

22:43.050 --> 22:45.905
- WELL, I DON'T REALLY FEEL
LIKE A ROTTEN MOTHER,

22:45.950 --> 22:49.158
BUT SORRY
YOU FELT LIKE THAT.

22:49.190 --> 22:52.466
- I DIDN'T MEAN YOU.
I WAS TALKING ABOUT ME.

22:52.500 --> 22:54.673
- MM.

22:54.710 --> 22:57.508
CAN WE JUST TALK ABOUT
SOMETHING DIFFERENT, YOU KNOW?

22:57.540 --> 22:58.746
I'D KIND OF LIKE TO TAKE
THE NIGHT OFF

22:58.790 --> 23:00.883
FROM THINKING ABOUT MY TEENAGE
DAUGHTER AND HER PROBLEMS.

23:00.930 --> 23:02.477
- LET'S NOT TALK
ABOUT ANY KIDS AT ALL.

23:02.510 --> 23:05.399
- ABSOLUTELY.
THIS IS CAREFREE NIGHT.

23:05.450 --> 23:06.587
[doorbell rings]
THIS IS LADIES' NIGHT.

23:06.620 --> 23:08.440
WE'RE GONNA HAVE
GIRLS' NIGHT.

23:08.490 --> 23:10.037
LET'S MAKE--
- HELLO, HELLO!

23:10.070 --> 23:11.207
- HI!
- HEY, LADIES.

23:11.250 --> 23:14.458
- THERE SHE IS,
THE BRIDE-TO-BE!

23:14.490 --> 23:16.629
OF COURSE,
THE LADY OF THE HOUR.

23:16.670 --> 23:18.422
- HELLO!

23:18.460 --> 23:20.599
- HELLO.
EVERYONE LOOKS GORGEOUS.

23:20.640 --> 23:24.497
- OKAY, SO THE BRIDE-TO-BE
HAS TO WEAR THIS!

23:24.540 --> 23:25.700
- OH, WOW.

23:25.740 --> 23:27.879
- IT'S YOUR PARTY!
- I'LL JUST PUT IT--

23:27.920 --> 23:29.228
UH, I NEED A MIRROR
TO PUT IT ON.

23:29.260 --> 23:30.704
- AFTER YOU HAVE A DRINK.

23:30.750 --> 23:32.433
- AND A DRINK.
- A DRINK.

23:32.480 --> 23:34.539
- YES. YES, YES, YES.
- I MADE MOJITOS.

23:34.580 --> 23:36.548
- AND THEY'RE GOOD.
- THEY ARE GOOD, RIGHT?

23:36.580 --> 23:38.229
- YEAH.

23:38.270 --> 23:40.204
- WE ALSO HAVE RED WINE,
WHITE WINE.

23:40.240 --> 23:43.585
- OH, I'M COMING.
- OKAY, DO YOU WANT A MOJITO?

23:46.490 --> 23:47.559
- HEY.

23:47.590 --> 23:49.524
- HEY.
YOU WANTED TO TALK TO ME?

23:49.560 --> 23:51.039
- I FIGURED IT OUT.

23:51.080 --> 23:53.799
- YOU FIGURED WHAT OUT--
COLD FUSION?

23:53.840 --> 23:54.943
[pen clatters]

23:54.980 --> 23:55.901
- NO.

23:55.950 --> 23:58.089
I FIGURED OUT WHAT TO DO
WITH THE COMPANY.

23:58.120 --> 24:00.566
- OH, OKAY.
WHAT, UH...

24:00.610 --> 24:01.747
WHAT'S, UH--WHAT'S ALL THIS?

24:01.780 --> 24:03.771
- ALL RIGHT, CHECK IT OUT.
THIS IS WHERE WE STARTED.

24:03.820 --> 24:06.152
ONE STORE
ON UNIVERSITY AVENUE

24:06.200 --> 24:09.055
WITH ONE SHOE--
ONE BRILLIANT, BRILLIANT DESIGN.

24:09.100 --> 24:10.579
- YEAH, I KNOW,
I WAS THERE.

24:10.620 --> 24:11.848
- I KNOW YOU WERE, MAN.

24:11.890 --> 24:13.266
I KNOW YOU WERE.

24:13.310 --> 24:14.709
AND THEN WE EXPANDED.

24:14.760 --> 24:17.649
TWO STORES, THREE STORES
- YEP.

24:17.690 --> 24:19.658
- THEN WE STARTED SELLING
TO CHAIN STORES.

24:19.690 --> 24:21.487
THEN THERE'S
THE ONLINE STORE, RIGHT?

24:21.520 --> 24:23.522
THE T&S CROSS-TRAINER.
- YEAH.

24:23.560 --> 24:24.868
- THE T&S AIR WALKER.

24:24.910 --> 24:26.480
- YEAH, WELL, YOU KNOW,
WE WERE DIVERSIFYING

24:26.530 --> 24:27.599
THE PRODUCT LINE
AT THE TIME.

24:27.630 --> 24:29.279
- AND WE WIPED OUT, DUDE.
- IT WAS A BIG SELLER.

24:29.320 --> 24:30.878
- WHO CARES?

24:30.910 --> 24:32.775
WE LOST THE MAGIC.

24:32.810 --> 24:35.529
GIMMICKS, MAN...

24:35.570 --> 24:39.529
GIMMICKS, THEY'RE JUST--
OH, I CAN'T STAND THEM.

24:39.580 --> 24:41.536
WHEN I BOUGHT MY FIRST PAIR
OF T&S SHOES,

24:41.580 --> 24:45.641
I WAS LIKE,
"YES, THIS IS ME.

24:45.690 --> 24:47.305
THIS IS WHO I AM."

24:47.340 --> 24:49.092
AND LOOK AT US NOW.

24:49.140 --> 24:51.608
LOOK AT WHAT WE'VE BECOME--

24:51.660 --> 24:53.275
JUST GIMMICKS...

24:53.310 --> 24:54.550
- UH-HU_H.
[wrapper crinkles]

24:54.590 --> 24:56.137
- AND CLUTTER.
- OKAY.

24:56.180 --> 24:58.523
- WE TOTALLY LOST
OUR WAY, MAN.

24:58.560 --> 25:00.596
MMM.

25:00.630 --> 25:01.972
[wrapper crinkles]

25:02.010 --> 25:03.978
- EDIBLE?

25:04.010 --> 25:06.217
- OKAY, THANK YOU.

25:06.260 --> 25:08.182
- IN 1999,
I BOUGHT MY FIRST PAIR

25:08.230 --> 25:09.800
OF T&S SURF-RIDERS,

25:09.850 --> 25:11.602
THE BEST DAMN SANDAL
EVER MADE, MAN.

25:11.640 --> 25:12.846
- AGREED.
THAT WAS A GREAT SHOE.

25:12.890 --> 25:16.269
- IT WAS A GREAT SHOE.

25:16.300 --> 25:19.303
ONE SHOE...
ONE SHOE, DUDE--

25:19.340 --> 25:21.649
THAT IS OUR MISSION.
- MM-HMM.

25:21.690 --> 25:24.898
WELL, YOU KNOW, CORY,

25:24.930 --> 25:26.818
THAT'S JUST NOT THE WAY
THIS BUSINESS

25:26.870 --> 25:27.962
REALLY WORKS ANYMORE.

25:28.000 --> 25:29.001
- EXACTLY.

25:29.040 --> 25:30.894
IT'S WHAT MADE T&S GREAT.

25:30.940 --> 25:33.591
IT'LL BE WHAT MAKES
IT GREAT AGAIN.

25:38.390 --> 25:40.779
- SOMETHING TO THINK ABOUT.
- I KNOW.

25:40.810 --> 25:42.152
- BY THE TIME JABBAR
GOES TO COLLEGE,

25:42.190 --> 25:43.703
WHO KNOWS HOW EXPENSIVE
IT'LL BE?

25:43.740 --> 25:45.560
- OH, THAT'S WHAT
I'M DEALING WITH RIGHT NOW.

25:45.610 --> 25:46.531
I QUIT MY JOB WITH ADAM

25:46.570 --> 25:48.322
BECAUSE I MAKE MORE IN TIPS
AT THE BAR.

25:48.370 --> 25:50.747
IT'S NOT MY DREAM,
BUT WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO?

25:50.790 --> 25:52.951
- WELL, NOW YOU HAVE TIME
TO PURSUE YOUR DREAM.

25:52.990 --> 25:54.093
- OH, OKAY, MOM.

25:54.130 --> 25:55.267
- OKAY.
- I'LL DO THAT BETWEEN SHIFTS.

25:55.310 --> 25:56.891
- I WAS THINKING
BEFORE DESSERT

25:56.930 --> 25:58.613
AND BEFORE WE OPEN
YOUR PRESENTS,

25:58.660 --> 25:59.581
WE WOULD PLAY THIS GAME.

25:59.620 --> 26:00.996
"TABLE TOPICS--

26:01.040 --> 26:03.065
QUESTIONS TO START
GREAT CONVERSATIONS."

26:03.110 --> 26:04.793
SO LET'S GO
TO THE TABLE.

26:04.830 --> 26:07.173
- WAIT, WE'RE AT THE TABLE,
AND WE HAVE TOPICS.

26:07.220 --> 26:08.699
- YES, BUT WE'RE DONE
WITH DINNER,

26:08.730 --> 26:09.936
AND WE'RE GONNA GO
TO THAT TABLE.

26:09.980 --> 26:11.208
- WE'RE HAVING A CONVERSATION.

26:11.250 --> 26:13.389
- AND THIS IS GONNA BE ANOTHER
DIFFERENT, FUN CONVERSATION.

26:13.430 --> 26:14.977
- OH! A DIFFERENT,
FUN ONE, OKAY.

26:15.020 --> 26:17.181
- COME ON, LET'S GO.
IT WILL BE FUN.

26:17.230 --> 26:19.698
- OH, MY GOODNESS.
- "TABLE TOPICS."

26:19.750 --> 26:20.910
CAN'T WAIT.

26:20.950 --> 26:23.089
- UH, HEY, JULES,
YOU KNOW WHAT?

26:23.130 --> 26:25.155
I'M ACTUALLY GONNA HEAD OUT.
I'VE--I'M--

26:25.200 --> 26:27.122
- OH, KRISTINA.
- I'M SO TIRED.

26:27.170 --> 26:29.309
I'VE HAD JUST
A REALLY LONG WEEK, AND I'M--

26:29.340 --> 26:30.409
- I'M SORRY.
YOU'RE MISSING DESSERT.

26:30.450 --> 26:31.826
- I KNOW. SAVE ME SOME.

26:31.860 --> 26:33.339
- LET HER GO.

26:33.380 --> 26:36.611
[whispering]
SHE HAS A LOT ON HER MIND.

26:36.660 --> 26:38.104
- I'M SORRY.
WHAT, CAMILLE? I--

26:38.140 --> 26:40.654
DID YOU SAY SOMETHING?

26:40.700 --> 26:42.622
'CAUSE I'M...

26:42.670 --> 26:44.171
- [normal voice] I JUST SAID
YOU HAVE A LOT ON YOUR MIND,

26:44.220 --> 26:47.280
AND IF YOU WANT TO GO,
YOU SHOULD BE ABLE TO GO.

26:47.320 --> 26:49.322
- THANK YOU.

26:49.360 --> 26:51.669
DINNER WAS DELICIOUS.

26:51.710 --> 26:53.769
I'LL SEE YA.

26:56.780 --> 26:59.715
[door opens, closes]

26:59.750 --> 27:02.127
- NO, YOU GOT TO GO
IN THAT HALF-PIPE.

27:02.170 --> 27:03.649
YOU GOT TO GO
IN FROM THE TOP.

27:03.690 --> 27:04.952
[doorbell rings]
- YEAH, I SAW THE BARREL.

27:05.000 --> 27:06.069
- IF YOU GO OVER--
HIT PAUSE.

27:06.100 --> 27:07.715
[knock at door]
IF YOU OLLIE IT,

27:07.760 --> 27:09.728
YOU GET EXTRA POINTS.

27:09.760 --> 27:11.068
- HEY, SORRY I'M LATE.

27:11.110 --> 27:12.441
I JUST GOT CALLED
INTO THE OFFICE.

27:12.490 --> 27:14.765
IT WAS A TOTAL AMBUSH.
IT WAS UNBELIEVABLE.

27:14.800 --> 27:16.006
BUT IT WAS
PRETTY MIND-BLOWING TOO,

27:16.040 --> 27:17.667
BECAUSE YOU REMEMBER
THAT BOSS THAT I HAVE

27:17.700 --> 27:19.042
WHO I THINK IS AN IDIOT,
BUT HE--

27:19.080 --> 27:20.047
YOU DON'T REMEMBER THAT GUY?

27:20.080 --> 27:21.047
WELL, HE'S NOT AN IDIOT.

27:21.080 --> 27:22.729
I MEAN, HE IS,
BUT HE'S NOT.

27:22.770 --> 27:24.738
HE'S GOT ALL
TH ESE WACKED-OUT CHARTS

27:24.780 --> 27:27.328
AND MUMBO JUMBO DRAWN
ALL OVER HIS OFFICE WALLS.

27:27.360 --> 27:29.749
IT MAKES ABSOLUTELY NO SENSE
WHATSOEVER

27:29.780 --> 27:31.748
UNTIL, BAM, IT HITS ME
LIKE A RAINBOW.

27:31.780 --> 27:32.917
YOU KNOW? YOU KNOW
HOW YOU ALWAYS THINK

27:32.960 --> 27:35.747
THE GRASS IS GREENER,
BUT YOU GET THERE, AND IT'S NOT?

27:35.790 --> 27:37.746
WELL, HE'S RIGHT.
HE'S RIGHT.

27:37.790 --> 27:40.167
- HIT YOU LIKE A RAINBOW?
- YEAH, HE'S RIGHT.

27:40.210 --> 27:43.441
THE GRASS IS GREENER WHEN WE GET
BACK TO BASICS AT T&S, OKAY?

27:43.480 --> 27:45.687
ALTHOUGH ONE SHOE,
WHICH IS WHAT HE WANTS TO DO,

27:45.730 --> 27:46.719
THAT'S INSANE.

27:46.760 --> 27:48.796
THAT IS IN-SANE--

27:48.830 --> 27:50.149
ONE SHOE.

27:50.180 --> 27:51.693
BUT WE DO HAVE TO GET
BACK TO THE CORE, YOU KNOW,

27:51.730 --> 27:53.379
OF WHAT T&S IS,
YOU KNOW WHAT I'M SAYING?

27:53.430 --> 27:54.761
- LET ME TAKE A LOOK
AT YOUR EYES.

27:54.810 --> 27:55.799
- OW, GOD!

27:55.840 --> 27:58.081
- DOUBLE RAINBOW,
LET ME LOOK AT YOUR EYES.

27:58.120 --> 27:59.326
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING
TO MY FACE?

27:59.360 --> 28:00.839
- WHAT HAVE YOU CONSUMED?
YOU'RE...

28:00.880 --> 28:02.427
YOU'RE WASTED, RIGHT?

28:02.470 --> 28:03.812
- NO, I'M NOT.

28:03.850 --> 28:05.465
- LISTEN, YOU'RE--
ARE YOU STONED?

28:05.510 --> 28:06.886
- COME ON, PLEASE, CROSBY.

28:06.920 --> 28:07.909
IS IT--
WHAT IS THAT?

28:07.960 --> 28:10.292
CAN I HAVE THAT?
- HEY! WHERE DID YOU GET THIS?

28:10.340 --> 28:11.432
- MY BOSS
GAVE IT TO ME.

28:11.480 --> 28:12.708
- YOUR BOSS GAVE YOU THIS?
- YEAH.

28:12.760 --> 28:13.784
- YOUR BOSS
GAVE YOU A LOLLIPOP.

28:13.830 --> 28:14.819
- YEAH, IT'S TANGERINE.

28:14.860 --> 28:16.828
- YOU SEE THIS?
- IT'S TANGERINE.

28:16.860 --> 28:18.202
JOEL, TASTE IT.
IT'S TANGERINE.

28:18.240 --> 28:19.138
- I'M NOT GONNA TASTE IT.

28:19.180 --> 28:21.865
- ADAM, DO YOU KNOW
WHAT AN EDIBLE IS?

28:21.900 --> 28:24.903
- I KNOW WHAT
AN EDIBLE COMPLEX IS.

28:24.940 --> 28:26.908
[laughing]

28:26.940 --> 28:28.737
- [laughing]

28:28.770 --> 28:30.180
- JOEL GOT IT.

28:30.220 --> 28:31.733
- YOU DON'T EVEN--
YOU'RE--

28:31.770 --> 28:33.806
BUDDY, YOU'RE...

28:33.850 --> 28:36.114
YOU'RE HIGH.

28:36.160 --> 28:37.491
- EDIBLE MARIJUANA--
THAT'S WHAT THIS IS.

28:37.540 --> 28:39.940
- THIS IS MEDICINAL MARIJUANA,

28:39.990 --> 28:41.389
AND I DON'T THINK YOU--
- HE DRUGGED ME?

28:41.440 --> 28:43.055
- YES.

28:43.100 --> 28:45.091
- SERIOUSLY,
HE SLIPPED ME A MICKEY?

28:45.130 --> 28:47.849
I'M HIGH.
- YOU'RE HIGH.

28:49.830 --> 28:54.176
- [laughing]

29:13.370 --> 29:14.883
- WHY AM I THE ONLY ONE
THAT THINKS

29:14.920 --> 29:19.402
THAT THIS IS
AN ACCIDENT WAITING TO HAPPEN?

29:19.440 --> 29:21.169
YOU DON'T.

29:21.200 --> 29:24.545
ADAM DOESN'T.

29:24.590 --> 29:26.990
HADDIE DEFINITELY DOESN'T.

29:29.490 --> 29:31.481
I JUST KNOW IN MY GUT,
CAMILLE,

29:31.520 --> 29:32.839
THAT I'M RIGHT ABOUT THIS.

29:32.870 --> 29:34.519
I JUST DO.

29:38.840 --> 29:40.831
I JUST...

29:45.300 --> 29:47.848
[crying]

29:56.550 --> 30:00.919
- WELL, I BROUGHT ADAM
UP HERE, CROSBY, DREW,

30:00.970 --> 30:05.066
AND NOW YOU, GRANDSON.

30:05.110 --> 30:08.557
AND EVERY TIME I'M UP HERE,
IT'S JUST SO BEAUTIFUL.

30:11.460 --> 30:16.045
I WISH THAT MY LIFE
HAD THAT KIND OF CLARITY.

30:22.060 --> 30:23.880
WHEN I GOT BACK
FROM VIETNAM,

30:23.920 --> 30:25.649
MY LIFE WAS A MESS.

30:25.680 --> 30:29.434
I WAS A MESS.

30:29.480 --> 30:32.540
YOUR GRANDMOTHER--
SHE HUNG IN THERE, THOUGH.

30:35.000 --> 30:37.412
SHE JUST LOVED ME, AND...

30:39.520 --> 30:42.489
SHE WOULDN'T LET ME GO.

30:42.530 --> 30:46.216
I THINK SHE SAVED
MY LIFE.

30:46.250 --> 30:50.528
- HAVE WE DONE EVERYTHING
WE'RE SUPPOSED TO DO?

30:50.570 --> 30:52.629
- WE HAVEN'T HAD
OUR HOT CHOCOLATE YET.

30:52.670 --> 30:55.184
- YOU SAID IF I WASN'T
HAVING A GOOD TIME,

30:55.230 --> 30:56.629
I COULD GO HOME.

30:56.680 --> 31:00.400
- YOU'RE NOT HA\l/\IICN)G A GOOD TIME?

31:00.440 --> 31:02.055
- THAT'S PROBABLY MY FAULT.

31:02.100 --> 31:03.169
I TALK TOO MUCH.

31:03.200 --> 31:05.953
- I JUST REALLY
WANT TO GO HOME.

31:06.000 --> 31:08.161
- WELL, WE GOT TO FINISH
THE MARSHMALLOWS,

31:08.210 --> 31:09.347
AND WE'RE GONNA
COUNT THE STARS.

31:09.380 --> 31:11.063
- I'M DONE
WITH THE MARSHMALLOWS.

31:11.110 --> 31:13.135
- WHAT ABOUT COUNTING
THE STARS?

31:13.180 --> 31:16.513
- I JUST WANT TO GO HOME!
NOW!

