I WANT TO GO HOME!

31:20.980 --> 31:23.289
I WANT TO GO HOME!
I WANT TO GO HOME!

31:23.320 --> 31:24.708
- MAX!
- I WANT TO GO HOME!

31:24.740 --> 31:27.083
I WANT TO GO HOME!
I WANT TO GO HOME!

31:27.120 --> 31:29.463
I WANT TO GO HOME!
I WANT TO GO HOME!

31:29.500 --> 31:31.559
I WANT TO GO HOME!

31:31.610 --> 31:34.056
- WHAT HISTORICAL TIME PERIOD
WOULD YOU LOVE TO LIVE IN?

31:34.090 --> 31:35.648
- THAT ONE'S SO BORING.

31:35.680 --> 31:37.500
- ANYTHING?
A STEP UP. LET'S--

31:37.550 --> 31:39.051
- WE'RE BACK.

31:39.100 --> 31:39.919
- HI.
- HI.

31:39.960 --> 31:41.928
- GOT ROOM FOR TWO MORE
IN THE GAME?

31:41.960 --> 31:44.167
- HI. I'M SO SORRY
THAT I RUINED YOUR PARTY.

31:44.210 --> 31:45.438
I HOPE
I DIDN'T RUIN IT.

31:45.480 --> 31:47.584
- YOU DIDN'T RUIN
ANYTHING, GIRL. SIT DOWN.

31:47.620 --> 31:49.099
- CAN I PLAY?
- HAVE A SEAT!

31:49.140 --> 31:50.698
WE'VE BEEN HAVING FUN.

31:50.730 --> 31:52.277
OKAY, HERE'S
THE NEXT QUESTION. READY?

31:52.320 --> 31:54.072
IF YOU COULD BRING
ONE FASHION ACCESSORY

31:54.110 --> 31:55.623
TO A DESERT ISLAND,
WHAT WOULD IT BE?

31:55.670 --> 31:57.149
- A PHONE TO CALL SOMEBODY

31:57.190 --> 31:58.521
TO GET ME
OFF THE DESERT ISLAND.

31:58.570 --> 31:59.707
- WHY WOULD YOU NEED

31:59.740 --> 32:01.219
A FASHION ACCESSORY
ON A DESERT ISLAND?

32:01.260 --> 32:03.637
- I DON'T KNOW.
- I'D BRING A SIX-PACK.

32:03.680 --> 32:05.466
- I'M GONNA DO
AN EYELASH CURLER.

32:05.500 --> 32:08.298
- SEE, EYELASH CURLER.
JASMINE'S PLAYING THE GAME.

32:08.340 --> 32:10.126
- AN EYELASH CURLER.

32:10.160 --> 32:12.640
- UH, HEY, LADIES.
[door closes]

32:12.680 --> 32:14.307
- HEY, THE BOYS ARE HERE.

32:14.340 --> 32:15.648
- HEY, UH...
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

32:15.690 --> 32:17.612
YOU CAN'T BE HERE.
- I KNOW WE CAN'T, BUT--

32:17.650 --> 32:19.129
- WELL, BABE.
WHAT IS HAPPENING?

32:19.170 --> 32:20.137
- YOU OKAY?
- HI.

32:20.170 --> 32:21.512
- HI.

32:21.560 --> 32:23.585
- OH, GOD, CAN YOU GET THEM
OUT OF HERE, PLEASE?

32:23.630 --> 32:25.723
- IS EVERYTHING OKAY?

32:25.770 --> 32:27.453
- YOU LOOK BEAUTIFUL.
- THANK YOU.

32:27.490 --> 32:28.593
- HONEY, WHAT'S WRONG?

32:28.630 --> 32:30.552
WHY ARE YOU--
- NOTHIN'.

32:30.600 --> 32:32.113
- THIS IS NOT SUPPOSED
TO HAPPEN RIGHT NOW.

32:32.150 --> 32:33.287
- EVERYTHING
IS NOT ALL RIGHT.

32:33.330 --> 32:34.661
- IT'S NOT ALL RIGHT?
- IT'S NOT.

32:34.710 --> 32:36.462
I MEAN, EVERYBODY'S FINE...

32:36.500 --> 32:37.569
- OKAY.
- AS IN SAFE.

32:37.610 --> 32:38.565
JUST HOLD ME.

32:38.610 --> 32:41.158
- HONEY, WHAT'S WRONG?
- JUST FOR A SECOND.

32:41.200 --> 32:42.155
- ARE YOU OKAY?
- IS HE OKAY?

32:42.200 --> 32:44.122
- OHH!
- HE'S FINE.

32:44.160 --> 32:45.604
HE'S BEYOND FINE.

32:45.650 --> 32:47.402
- ADAM!
- I'M SO CONFUSED.

32:47.440 --> 32:48.748
- OKAY, THAT'S FOR THE GUESTS
OF THE PARTY.

32:48.790 --> 32:50.189
- [mouth full]
I'M JUST HUNGRY, JULIA.

32:50.240 --> 32:52.026
SORRY.

32:54.350 --> 32:56.682
HONEY, I'M SCARED.
- OF WHAT?

32:56.730 --> 32:58.448
- OF US JUST SPLITTING
APART AT THE SEAMS.

32:58.490 --> 33:00.549
WE'VE NEVER DISAGREED
ABOUT ANYTHING LIKE THIS BEFORE.

33:02.150 --> 33:05.005
- HE--HE'S A LITTLE MORE
PARANOID THAN NORMAL.

33:05.050 --> 33:06.494
- YEAH.
- WHY?

33:06.530 --> 33:08.418
- [whispering]
BECAUSE HE'S--HE'S BAKED.

33:08.460 --> 33:09.734
- 'CAUSE I'M BAKED.

33:09.780 --> 33:12.738
- YOU'RE STONED?
- [laughing]

33:12.780 --> 33:15.465
- I FEEL LIKE I'M ON GRASS.
- MY BOSS DRUGGED ME.

33:15.510 --> 33:17.011
- HUH?
- MY BOSS DRUGGED ME.

33:17.060 --> 33:19.290
- I'M NOT SURPRISED.
- AND I WANTED TO SEE YOU.

33:19.340 --> 33:20.716
SO THEN MY FRIENDS
BROUGHT ME HERE.

33:20.750 --> 33:22.684
I MEAN, THEY'RE MY BROTHER
AND MY BROTHER-IN-LAW.

33:22.720 --> 33:24.642
- THAT'S SO FLATTERING.
- THAT'S SO SWEET.

33:24.690 --> 33:26.169
- JULIA,
THESE ARE REALLY GOOD.

33:26.210 --> 33:27.234
- OH, THANK YOU.

33:27.280 --> 33:28.417
- DO YOU HAVE ANY MORE?

33:28.450 --> 33:29.656
- NO, I DON'T.
- THESE ARE DELISH!

33:29.690 --> 33:30.725
COME ON, JULIA!

33:30.760 --> 33:32.512
DID YOU MAKE THEM?
- YES.

33:32.560 --> 33:33.652
- YOU'RE A GOOD COOK.

33:33.700 --> 33:35.554
- IN THE KITCHEN.
- AH, THE KITCHEN!

33:35.590 --> 33:38.047
- WHOO!
- AWESOME!

33:38.080 --> 33:39.217
- HI.

33:39.250 --> 33:40.660
- HI.
HOW'S YOUR PARTY?

33:40.700 --> 33:41.735
- FABULOUS.

33:41.770 --> 33:43.283
- OHH!
- OKAY, NO.

33:43.330 --> 33:45.639
OH, ADAM, NO,
THAT'S NOT FOR YOU!

33:45.670 --> 33:46.602
- OH!

33:46.640 --> 33:49.120
YOU GUYS, THESE CRAB CAKES
ARE ORGASMIC.

33:49.160 --> 33:51.674
- THANK YOU. I WORKED
REALLY HARD ON THOSE, BUT--

33:51.710 --> 33:53.849
- HEY, TORY...
CORY TOLD ME YOU QUIT.

33:53.890 --> 33:55.573
- UGH. I--YEAH.

33:55.610 --> 33:56.850
- I JUST WANT YOU TO KNOW
THAT I SUPPORT

33:56.890 --> 33:58.403
WHATEVER YOU CHOOSE
TO DO NEXT,

33:58.450 --> 34:00.759
'CAUSE YOU ARE LIKE
THE GREAT WANDERING BRAVERMAN,

34:00.790 --> 34:02.826
AND I LOVE YOU, OKAY?

34:02.860 --> 34:03.849
- THANKS.

34:03.900 --> 34:05.583
- WHO WANTS PIZZA?

34:05.620 --> 34:07.588
- OKAY, WHY DON'T YOU GUYS
TAKE ADAM HOME

34:07.630 --> 34:08.767
AND ORDER SOME PIZZA?

34:08.800 --> 34:10.620
BECAUSE IF YOU HAPPENED
TO READ THE EMBOSSED INVITATION,

34:10.660 --> 34:13.595
THIS IS--THIS IS
A FEMALE-ONLY EVENING.

34:13.630 --> 34:15.211
THIS EVENT IS GIRLS ONLY.
- JULIA, LOOK AT HIM.

34:15.260 --> 34:18.252
- JULIA, I AM NEVER
LEAVING THIS KITCHEN.

34:18.290 --> 34:21.259
I AM HUNGRY, AND THIS
IS THE BEST FOOD EVER.

34:21.300 --> 34:23.609
[David Bowie's Let's Dance]

34:23.640 --> 34:27.508
- UH-OH! BRAVERMAN
FAVORITE PASTIME!

34:27.540 --> 34:29.679
- IT'S TIME
TO OPEN PRESENTS.

34:29.720 --> 34:31.711
- OH, NO!
OH, CHIPPENDALES.

34:31.750 --> 34:35.641
OH, NO, BE MY BOYFRIEND,
MOM, LET'S GO.

34:35.690 --> 34:37.783
- THIS IS SO WEIRD.

34:37.830 --> 34:40.481
- GET IT.
- ARE YOU--

34:40.520 --> 34:42.135
- I'M NOT DANCING.
HERE YOU GO.

34:42.180 --> 34:44.728
- YOU ARE SO WEIRD.

34:44.770 --> 34:45.839
WHO ARE YOU?

34:45.870 --> 34:46.905
- PRINCESS LEIA.

34:46.940 --> 34:48.350
- WHOA, WHOA, WHOA,
WHOA, WHOA!

34:48.390 --> 34:49.869
MY CROTCH
IS VIBRATING.

34:49.910 --> 34:51.525
- HONEY, IT'S YOUR PHONE.
- HONEY.

34:51.570 --> 34:52.730
- THERE'S NOTHING
VIBRATING HERE.

34:52.780 --> 34:54.281
- I GOT--I GOT IT.

34:54.330 --> 34:56.321
- AY, YI, YI.

34:56.370 --> 34:57.746
- HOLY CRAP, IT'S DAD.

34:57.780 --> 35:00.294
I'M GONNA ANSWER THIS.
- HONEY, I SHOULD TALK TO HIM.

35:00.330 --> 35:01.888
- NO, HONEY.
I'VE GOT IT, I'VE GOT IT.

35:01.920 --> 35:03.535
I'VE GOT IT, I'M OKAY.
I'VE GOT IT.

35:03.580 --> 35:04.808
HEY, CAN WE TURN DOWN
THE MUSIC?

35:04.860 --> 35:07.306
IT'S DAD.
- IT'S PROBABLY ABOUT MAX.

35:07.340 --> 35:08.887
- HOLD ON, HOLD ON, OKAY.
[ringing continues]

35:08.930 --> 35:10.716
- YOU SHOULDN'T LET HIM
ANSWER IT.

35:10.760 --> 35:12.239
- I KNOW I SHOULDN'T.
- HELLO.

35:12.280 --> 35:14.202
- HEY, SONNY.
OH, BOY, DO WE HAVE A PROBLEM.

35:14.250 --> 35:16.241
- WHAT?
- MAX WANTS TO COME HOME.

35:16.280 --> 35:17.508
- WELL, WHAT'S THE PROBLEM?

35:17.560 --> 35:19.903
- WELL, LOOK, KID,
I DID EVERYTHING

35:19.940 --> 35:21.555
HE WANTED TO DO, ALL RIGHT?

35:21.600 --> 35:23.352
I MEAN, WE GOT HERE,
HE WANTED TO LOOK FOR BUGS

35:23.390 --> 35:24.948
BEFORE WE PITCHED THE TENT--
I DID THAT.

35:24.980 --> 35:26.663
HE WANTED TO HAVE
THE MARSHMALLOWS

35:26.710 --> 35:28.598
BEFORE WE COUNTED THE STARS--
I DID THAT.

35:28.640 --> 35:30.426
COME ON, I'VE DONE EVERYTHING
HE WANTED TO DO.

35:30.470 --> 35:32.563
- YEAH. DAD, YOU GAVE HIM
HIS PAYCHECK

35:32.610 --> 35:33.531
BEFORE HE DID HIS WORK.

35:33.570 --> 35:35.151
YOU HAVE TO DO IT
THE OTHER WAY AROUND.

35:35.200 --> 35:36.747
- OKAY, DON'T TELL ME.

35:36.780 --> 35:38.429
THAT'S IN KRISTINA'S
INSTRUCTION MANUAL, ISN'T IT?

35:38.480 --> 35:39.811
- YEAH. YOU HAVE TO READ
THAT MANUAL RIGHT NOW.

35:39.860 --> 35:41.612
I WANT TO TALK TO MAX.
- COVER TO COVER.

35:41.650 --> 35:42.856
I TOLD HIM THAT.
- YEAH, SURE.

35:42.890 --> 35:46.371
MAX, YOUR DAD
WANTS TO TALK TO YOU.

35:46.420 --> 35:49.890
THERE YOU GO.

35:49.940 --> 35:50.759
- HEY, MAX.
- UH-HUH?

35:50.800 --> 35:52.552
- HEY, BUDDY,
WHAT'S THE PROBLEM?

35:52.590 --> 35:54.797
- I-I JUST REALLY
WANT TO GO HOME.

35:54.840 --> 35:57.172
- [whispers] WANTS TO GO HOME.
- OH, HONEY, THEN LET HIM.

35:57.220 --> 36:00.496
LET HIM.
I'LL GO PICK HIM UP.

36:00.530 --> 36:02.566
- MAX, I TELL YOU WHAT.

36:02.600 --> 36:04.568
IF YOU WANT TO COME HOME,
YOU ABSOLUTELY CAN.

36:04.610 --> 36:07.875
BUT IF YOU DO,

36:07.920 --> 36:09.649
YOU'RE GONNA MISS
SOMETHING REALLY SPECIAL.

36:09.680 --> 36:11.784
- WHAT?

36:11.820 --> 36:13.674
- IN THE MORNING

36:13.720 --> 36:15.688
WHEN THE SUN COMES UP
ON THE CREEK,

36:15.720 --> 36:17.369
ALL THE LACEWINGS COME OUT--

36:17.410 --> 36:19.298
HUNDREDS OF THEM,
THOUSANDS.

36:19.340 --> 36:21.900
AND DO YOU STILL HAVE
THAT SPECIMEN JAR WITH YOU,

36:21.930 --> 36:23.340
THE ONE THAT MOM
PACKED FOR YOU?

36:23.380 --> 36:24.893
- YEAH, I'VE GOT IT.
- OKAY.

36:24.940 --> 36:25.929
DO YOU WANT
TO COLLECT SOME,

36:25.970 --> 36:27.961
PUT THEM IN A JAR,
AND THEN BRING THEM HOME?

36:28.010 --> 36:29.523
- YEAH.
- OKAY.

36:29.560 --> 36:30.902
WELL, THE DECISION
IS YOURS,

36:30.940 --> 36:32.623
BUT I KNOW I WOULD REALLY
LIKE TO SEE

36:32.670 --> 36:34.809
A COUPLE
OF THOSE BAD BOYS.

36:39.950 --> 36:42.259
- OKAY, WE CAN STAY.

36:52.960 --> 36:58.239
- AS THE BLACKBIRD
IN THE SPRING

36:58.280 --> 37:02.967
'NEATH THE WILLOW TREE

37:03.010 --> 37:05.979
[humming]

37:21.340 --> 37:24.685
AURA LEA

37:26.690 --> 37:31.582
MAID OF GOLDEN HAIR

37:31.620 --> 37:37.069
SUNSHINE CAME
ALONG WITH THEE

37:37.110 --> 37:43.595
AND FLOWERS
IN HER HAIR

37:43.640 --> 37:45.665
[truck approaches]

37:45.710 --> 37:46.734
- I'M SO EXCITED TO SEE HIM.

37:46.780 --> 37:47.599
[horn honks]
- HEY!

37:47.640 --> 37:49.870
- HI, GUYS.
- WHOO-HOO. ALL RIGHT.

37:49.920 --> 37:51.979
MAX.
- HEY.

37:52.020 --> 37:53.294
HI, BUDDY.

37:53.340 --> 37:54.887
- LOOK.
I CAUGHT 40 OF 'EM.

37:54.920 --> 37:56.672
- REALLY? YOU DID IT.
- 40? WOW.

37:56.720 --> 37:58.301
- ALL RIGHT.
- WHAT ARE THESE CALLED?

37:58.340 --> 37:59.432
- LACEWINGS.
- LACEWINGS.

37:59.480 --> 38:00.572
- LACEWINGS?
- YES.

38:00.620 --> 38:01.689
- THEY'RE LIKE
LITTLE GRASSHOPPERS.

38:01.720 --> 38:03.995
- NO, NO, THEY'RE
NOT LIKE GRASSHOPPERS AT ALL.

38:04.040 --> 38:05.689
- OKAY, LET'S GET YOU INSIDE
AND GET YOU CLEANED UP.

38:05.730 --> 38:06.924
- NO, I DON'T WANT
TO GET CLEANED UP.

38:06.970 --> 38:09.006
- MAX, THEY LOOK GREAT.
- SAY THANKS TO GRANDPA.

38:09.040 --> 38:10.655
- THANKS, GRANDPA.
[door opens, closes]

38:10.700 --> 38:14.739
- MM-HMM.

38:14.770 --> 38:16.499
- WELL, GRAN DPA?

38:16.530 --> 38:17.804
- [laughs]

38:17.840 --> 38:19.353
- YOU DID IT.
YOU TOOK MAX CAMPING.

38:19.400 --> 38:21.709
- YEAH, YEAH,
I SURE DID.

38:21.740 --> 38:23.367
HAD A FEW HICCUPS THERE.

38:23.400 --> 38:25.675
- MM-HMM.

38:25.710 --> 38:27.644
- THANKS FOR THE ASSIST.

38:27.680 --> 38:31.366
- THAT'S WHAT I'M HERE FOR.

38:31.410 --> 38:34.618
- MAN...

38:34.650 --> 38:37.778
I GOT A BETTER IDEA OF WHAT
YOU AND KRISTINA GO THROUGH.

38:39.480 --> 38:41.789
- YEAH, WELL,

38:41.830 --> 38:44.890
HE CAN BE A HANDFUL,
THAT'S FOR SURE.

38:44.940 --> 38:48.694
THAT'S WHY WE SENT
THAT INSTRUCTION MANUAL ALONG.

38:48.740 --> 38:50.765
- YEAH.

38:50.810 --> 38:52.949
- HOPE YOU GUYS
HAD A GOOD TIME.

38:52.980 --> 38:55.847
- HE'S A WONDERFUL BOY.

39:12.100 --> 39:13.135
- HI.

39:13.170 --> 39:15.798
- HI.

39:15.830 --> 39:17.866
- HEY, ADAM?
- YEAH?

39:17.900 --> 39:19.936
- HADDIE'S--

39:22.770 --> 39:24.863
- HEY.
- HEY.

39:24.910 --> 39:27.765
UH, THANKS FOR BRINGING
MY CLOTHES OVER.

39:27.810 --> 39:29.801
- OH, YOU'RE WELCOME.

39:34.610 --> 39:36.464
- UH, OKAY, WELL, I...

39:36.510 --> 39:38.501
I FEEL REALLY STUPID
ABOUT TELLING YOU

39:38.540 --> 39:39.984
THAT I CHOOSE ALEX
OVER YOU.

39:40.030 --> 39:42.476
IT'S RIDICULOUS.
I MEAN--

39:42.510 --> 39:43.886
- IT'S OKAY. IT'S FINE.

39:43.930 --> 39:46.649
- I LOVE YOU GUYS.

39:46.690 --> 39:47.759
I MISS YOU.

39:47.790 --> 39:49.792
I'M SORRY.
I'M REALLY SORRY

39:49.830 --> 39:54.585
THAT I SAID SOME MEAN
AND STUPID THINGS TO YOU,

39:54.630 --> 39:57.736
BUT ALSO, YOU KNOW,
YOU GUYS HAVE TO KNOW

39:57.770 --> 39:59.738
THAT YOU'RE WRONG
ABOUT ALEX.

39:59.770 --> 40:04.798
AND I AM NOT SORRY
THAT I MOVED OUT,

40:04.850 --> 40:06.158
AND I WANT YOU TO KNOW

40:06.190 --> 40:08.602
THAT I'M GONNA STAY
AT GRANDMA AND GRANDPA'S

40:08.640 --> 40:10.084
OFFICIALLY.

40:19.170 --> 40:22.139
[mellow rock music]

40:26.180 --> 40:28.865
- WELL, THE YOUNG SPORTSMAN
IS ASLEEP.

40:28.900 --> 40:30.003
- MM.

40:30.040 --> 40:33.521
- MRS. TRUSSEL,
LOOK AT THIS.

40:33.560 --> 40:35.801
WELL, WELL,
WHERE DID THIS COME FROM?

40:35.840 --> 40:37.182
- JUST ONE OF MY GIFTS
THAT I DIDN'T GET A CHANCE

40:37.220 --> 40:38.209
TO OPEN LAST NIGHT.

40:38.260 --> 40:39.807
- OH, BOY.
- MM-HMM.

40:39.850 --> 40:41.568
- DO YOU HAVE ANY MORE
THAT YOU WANT TO SHOW ME?

40:41.610 --> 40:43.635
- OH, YEAH.
- OOH, CAN I SEE?

40:43.680 --> 40:46.126
- SHALL I DO A LITTLE
LINGERIE FASHION SHOW FOR YOU?

40:46.160 --> 40:47.912
- YES, PLEASE.

40:54.760 --> 40:55.966
- ALL RIGHT.
YOU READY?

40:56.000 --> 40:57.820
- LIFE IS GOOD.

40:57.860 --> 40:59.896
MMM! MM-HMM.

40:59.940 --> 41:00.895
I'M FEELING IT.

41:00.940 --> 41:03.864
MMM!
DELICIOUS.

41:03.900 --> 41:05.788
- AND HOW ABOUT THIS ONE?

41:05.840 --> 41:09.526
- YEAH, THAT COLOR
MAKES YOUR WHATEVER POP.

41:09.570 --> 41:10.901
- [laughing]

41:10.950 --> 41:12.804
- ALL RIGHT.

41:22.160 --> 41:23.787
- HEY.

41:23.820 --> 41:26.618
- HEY, HONEY.

41:26.650 --> 41:27.639
- YOU OKAY?

41:31.970 --> 41:33.892
- YOU KNOW, MY MOM...

41:33.930 --> 41:36.967
RAN AWAY WITH MY DAD
WHEN SHE WAS 16.

41:38.870 --> 41:40.906
- YEAH, I FORGET
SHE WAS THAT YOUNG.

41:42.940 --> 41:46.944
- HE MADE HER SO MISERABLE
EVERY SINGLE DAY OF HER LIFE.

41:46.980 --> 41:50.108
- HADDIE
IS NOT GONNA RUN OFF

41:50.160 --> 41:51.878
AND GET MARRIED
TO ALEX.

41:51.920 --> 41:55.048
- YOU DON'T KNOW THAT, HONEY.

41:55.090 --> 41:56.842
YOU SHOULD SEE
HOW SHE LOOKS AT HIM.

41:56.890 --> 41:58.198
YOU HAVE NO IDEA.

41:58.230 --> 42:01.609
- KRISTINA, WE'RE NOT
GONNA LOSE OUR DAUGHTER.

42:01.650 --> 42:02.753
OKAY?

42:06.930 --> 42:08.659
- I JUST DON'T KNOW
WHAT TO DO.

42:08.690 --> 42:10.248
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT TO DO RIGHT NOW.

42:10.280 --> 42:12.623
- NEITHER DO I.

42:15.390 --> 42:17.597
ALL I KNOW
IS I MISS OUR LITTLE GIRL,

42:17.630 --> 42:19.632
AND I WANT HER
TO COME HOME.

42:22.120 --> 42:23.849
- ME TOO.
